article.description: Stanley Umude matched his season high with 21 points as South Dakota easily defeated NAIA-member Mayville State 96-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Umude leads South Dakota past Mayville State 96-60
article.linkText: Umude leads South Dakota past Mayville State 96-60
article.story: VERMILLION, S.D. -- Stanley Umude matched his season high with 21 points as South Dakota easily defeated NAIA-member Mayville State 96-60 on Saturday. Tyler Hagedorn had 16 points and 11 rebounds for South Dakota (9-3), which earned its fifth straight home victory. Tyler Peterson added 16 points and Cody Kelley had 13. The 96 points were a season best for South Dakota. Max Cooper had 12 points for the Comets and Rene Melendez added 10. South Dakota faces Northern Colorado on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
